parameters: ......I want to investigate what I saw before here.
......I want to investigate what I saw before here.

I knew from the sign that it was a restroom. However, the door was
still dark and closed even in this dark building. My instinct tells me
to leave. ...However, I can't just leave here.
With determination, I reach out with trembling hands--
--I strangely felt relieved that the door didn't open.

......Something is falling. -- It's a hairpin. It's brand new. It's falling
on the edge of the toilet bowl. A common hairpin. However, I also know
that Araka likes to wear hairpins.

In normal circumstances, it's a place where you wouldn't have the
opportunity to enter in your lifetime. As I hesitantly reach out my
hand towards it, I notice a strange sound coming from inside.

I have a bad feeling. I listen carefully and bring my head closer to
the door. It's a sound that resembles the cries of a cat and a mouse,
but with a distorted noise.

When I realized that, I felt as if ice had been injected into my
spine. -- This is the cry of a baby. And not just any baby. It is not
a cry of bright life, but one filled with resentment and hatred.

Although it was clear that it was the voice of a baby, it was far from
being a normal baby.

Because... like a newborn baby, it is the sound of crying.
However, it is laughing. With a terribly grating noise.

Slowly, I move away from the door, trying not to be noticed
by whatever is inside. Even if it's dull, I understand that if I'm
noticed, it will be the end of the story.

......A ominous... voice can only be described as a baby, can be heard.
There is no doubt that there is something inside. There is no doubt
that there is a clue--
As soon as I muttered, Alright--the crying sound abruptly stopped.

The field of vision flickers--the heart stops in fear. I was noticed--
just that, I sensed the emotions directed towards me.
It was an overwhelmingly strong pleasure.
--Within fading consciousness, I heard the laughter of an old woman.

--No. I shake my head and quietly move away from the door. If I'm
noticed, it will surely be over.
I shouldn't enter here... Just knowing that is enough, right?

Fluffy white cards are floating. It is an unusual sight, but I don't
feel any ominousness. On the contrary, everything in this abandoned
building, which is filled with impurity, seems to be the first pure
thing I have ever seen.
──In addition, it closely resembled Araka's amulet.

You must not proceed any further. Because you too... will become
unable to return.
Go back to the first floor right away──

Use this at the entrance of the building... You can still go back
now...

There might be some clues here. It might be worth investigating
further.
